  h1.splash.docs-page-header Forms

  section.docs-section#styles
    h1.docs-h3 Form Styles
    p.
      Each row is wrapped within a <code>form-row</code> class. A form is designed such
      that by default it will expand to fill the parent div unless a width is given to
      the form (<em>Hint: Grids!</em>).


    article.docs-article#vertical
      h3.docs-h3 Vertical Layout
      p.
        The Aegis forms are generally laid out in a vertical fashion, with labels above
        their fields, and the form is scanned in a top-down manner.

      .example.docs-eg
        form.col-6.docs-eg-object
          fieldset
            legend Full Form Functionality
            .form-row
              label(for="username") Username
              .field-wrapper
                input#username(type="text")
                aside.field-help
                  p Let's see how field-help works.

            .form-row
              label(for="password")Password
              .field-wrapper
                input#password(type="password")
                aside.field-help
                  p Please enter your password.
            .form-row
              .field-wrapper">
                input(type="checkbox") Remember Me
                aside.field-help
                  p So you see how field-help works?
            .form-row
              .form-actions
                button.button.primary Log In
        pre.docs-eg-code.
          &lt;form&gt;
          &lt;div class="form-row"&gt;
            &lt;label for="username"&gt;Username&lt;/label&gt;
            &lt;div class="field-wrapper"&gt;
              &lt;input id='username' type="text"&gt;
              &lt;aside class="field-help"&gt;
                &lt;p&gt;Let's see how field-help works.&lt;/p&gt;
              &lt;/aside&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;div class="form-row"&gt;
            &lt;label for="password"&gt;Password&lt;/label&gt;
            &lt;div class="field-wrapper"&gt;
              &lt;input id='password' type="password"&gt;
              &lt;aside class="field-help"&gt;
                &lt;p&gt;Please enter your password.&lt;/p&gt;
              &lt;/aside&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;div class="form-row"&gt;
            &lt;div class="field-wrapper"&gt;
              &lt;input type="checkbox"&gt;Remember Me&lt;/input&gt;
              &lt;aside class="field-help"&gt;
                &lt;p&gt;So you see how field-help works?&lt;/p&gt;
              &lt;/aside&gt;
