  section.docs-section#standard
    h1.docs-h1 Standard Elements

    article.docs-article#text-input
      h3.docs-h3 Text Inputs
      p.
        Text inputs are omnipresent, from the username and password fields strewn
        all around, to nearly all related fields like search, email, url, tel,
        date, time, month, week, datetime, datetime-local, and number.

      .example.docs-eg
        form.alpha.col-6.docs-eg-object
          .form-row
            label(for="text") Text Input
            .field-wrapper
              input#text(type="text")
        pre.docs-eg-code.
          &lt;input type='text'&gt;

    article.docs-article#textarea
      h3.docs-h3 Textarea
      p.
        Textarea inputs follow the same styles of normal text inputs.
        They can be resized vertically.

      .example.docs-eg
        form.alpha.col-6.docs-eg-object
          .form-row
            label(for="textarea-field") Textarea
            .field-wrapper
              textarea#textarea-field
        pre.docs-eg-code.
          &lt;input type='text'&gt;

    article.docs-article#checkbox-radio
      h3.docs-h3 Checkboxes &amp; Radios
      p.
        Checkboxes are used for selecting multiple items from a given set, whereas Radio buttons allow only one item to be selected. Checkboxes are rendered in a stacked formation, whereas radio-buttons of a group are rendered side-by-side as long as there is horizontal space available.

      .example.docs-eg
        form.alpha.col-6.docs-eg-object.form-horizontal
          label(for='wolverine')
            input#wolverine(type="checkbox", value="wolverine", name="xmen", checked)
            | Wolverine
          label(for="cyclops")
            input#cyclops(type="checkbox", value="cyclops", name="xmen")
            | Cyclops
          label(for="apocalypse").disabled
            input#apocalypse(type="checkbox", value="apocalypse", name="xmen", disabled)
            | Apocalypse
          label(for="expanding")
            input#expanding(type="radio", name="universe", value="expanding", checked)
            | Expanding
          label(for="contracting")
            input#contracting(type="radio", name="universe", value="contracting")
            | Contracting
        pre.docs-eg-code.
          &lt;label for='wolverine'&gt;
            &lt;input type="checkbox" id="wolverine" value="wolverine" name="xmen" checked&gt; Wolverine &lt;/input&gt;
          &lt;/label&gt;

          &lt;label for="cyclops"&gt;
            &lt;input type="checkbox" id="cyclops" value="cyclops" name="xmen"&gt; Cyclops &lt;/input&gt;
          &lt;/label&gt;

          &lt;label for="apocalypse" class='disabled'&gt;
            &lt;input type="checkbox" id="apocalypse" value="apocalypse" name="xmen" disabled&gt; Apocalypse &lt;/input&gt;
          &lt;/label&gt;

          &lt;label for="expanding"&gt;
            &lt;input type="radio" id="expanding" name="universe" value="expanding" checked&gt; Expanding &lt;/input&gt;
          &lt;/label&gt;

          &lt;label for="contracting"&gt;
            &lt;input type="radio" id="contracting" name="universe" value="contracting"&gt; Contracting &lt;/input&gt;
          &lt;/label&gt;

    article.docs-article#select
      h3.docs-h3 Select Boxes
      p.
        Select boxes allow you to select an option from a given list.

      .example.docs-eg
        form.alpha.col-6.docs-eg-object
          .form-row
            label(for="select") Choose Your Enemy
            .field-wrapper
              select#select
                option(value="???") Joker
                option(value="edward") Riddler
                option(value="victorF") Mr. Freeze
                option(value="bane") Bane
                option(value="victorZ") Zsasz
        pre.docs-eg-code.
          &lt;select id="select"&gt;
            &lt;option value="???"&gt;Joker&lt;/option&gt;
            &lt;option value="edward"&gt;Riddler&lt;/option&gt;
            &lt;option value="victorF"&gt;Mr. Freeze&lt;/option&gt;
            &lt;option value="bane"&gt;Bane&lt;/option&gt;
            &lt;option value="victorZ"&gt;Zsasz&lt;/option&gt;
          &lt;/select&gt;

  section.docs-section#new
    h1.docs-h1 New Elements
    p.
      Aegis adds some additional form elements to this standard set.
      To use these elements, you'll have to include the corresponding plugin
      scripts in your page within a <code>&lt;script&gt;</code> tag.
      For example, if your want to add a multiselect input, you need to include
      <code>aegis-multiselect.js</code> to your page.

    article.docs-article#snippet
      h3.docs-h3 Snippets
      p.
        Snippets are small bits of information which you'd like users to select,
        copy and paste somewhere. Some use cases are presenting IDs or application
        secrets for developers to copy/paste in their code. To turn any text into a
        snippet, surround it with a <code>.snippet</code> span. You can also add a
        <code>.select-snippet</code> button next to the <code>.snippet</code> span to
        give users a more clear way to select the text. Note that right now, clicking on
        the snippet class only selects the text, but does not copy it. Javascript is not
        allowed (yet) to directly access the clipboad, but hopefully this operation will
        be <a href='http://www.w3.org/TR/clipboard-apis/'>supported soon</a>.
        Till then, <code>Ctrl+C</code> is your friend.

      p.hl.
        Remember to include the <code>aegis-snippets.js</code> file in your code to
        use this feature

      .example.docs-eg
        form.docs-eg-object col-9 alpha
          .form-row
            .field-wrapper
              span.snippet.alpha(title="Click on the text to copy it").
                This is some random text which can be copied in one click
              a.button.inline.select-snippet Select
          pre.docs-eg-code.
            &lt;form&gt;
              &lt;div class="form-row"&gt;
                &lt;div class="field-wrapper"&gt;
                  &lt;span class="snippet" title="Click on the text to copy it"&gt;
                    This is some random text which can be copied in one click
                  &lt;/span&gt;
                  &lt;a class="button inline select-snippet"&gt;Select&lt;/a&gt;
                &lt;/div&gt;
              &lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;/form&gt;


  section.docs-section#addons
    h1.docs-h1 Addons
    p.
      In addition to all the form-elements listed above, here are some
      nifty addons to make your forms more user-friendly.

    article.docs-article#field-help
      h3.docs-h3 Field Help
      p.
        As shown above, field helps are used to provide guidance to the user while
        filling the form in the form of tooltips. You can use tooltips by adding
        another element beside the input field with a <code>.field-help</code> class.

      .example.docs-eg
        form.alpha.col-6.docs-eg-object
          .form-row
            label(for="select") Choose Your Enemy
            .field-wrapper
              select#select
                option(value="hush") Hush
                option(value="ras-al-ghul") Raʾs al-Ġūl
                option(value="scarecrow") Scarecrow
              aside.field-help Choose your most-feared nightmare
        pre.docs-eg-code.
          &lt;select id="select"&gt;
            &lt;option value="hush"&gt;Hush&lt;/option&gt;
            &lt;option value="ras-al-ghul"&gt;Raʾs al-Ġūl&lt;/option&gt;
            &lt;option value="scarecrow"&gt;Scarecrow&lt;/option&gt;
          &lt;/select&gt;
          &lt;aside class="field-help"&gt;Choose your most-feared nightmare&lt;/aside&gt;




    article.docs-article#form-help
      h3.docs-h3 Form Help
      p.
        Also provided is a general help text for the whole form. Use it by
        adding the <code>.form-help</code> class to a span or div.

      .example.docs-eg
        form.alpha.col-6.docs-eg-object
          .form-row
            label(for="select") Choose Your Enemy
            .field-wrapper
              select#select
                option(value="hush") Dr. Strange
                option(value="ras-al-ghul") Raʾs al-Ġūl
                option(value="scarecrow") Joker
              aside.field-help Choose wisely... The symbol of the bat is at stake!
          .form-row
            .form-help We know your identity Bruce!
          .form-row
            .form-actions
              button.button.alert Fight
        pre.docs-eg-code.
          &lt;div class="form-row"&gt;
            &lt;div class="form-help"&gt;We know your identity Bruce!&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;
